=C2=A0<em>impression=C2=A0</em>of hugeness, and part of that comes from Alt=
man going around always saying the biggest possible number.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But I suppose that does create an opportunity =
for <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34493478.28537=
9/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS90ZWNoL2FpL3RoZS05LW1vbnRoLW9sZC1haS1zdGFydHVwL=
WNoYWxsZW5naW5nLXNpbGljb24tdmFsbGV5cy1naWFudHMtZWUyZTRjNDg_bW9kPWl0cF93c2o/=
607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB7ad64af3" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"item=
scope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !im=
portant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bot=
tom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> someone with a contrarian view<=
/a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">[Arthur]=C2=A0Mensch=E2=80=99s startup, called=
=C2=A0Mistral AI, is challenging the conventional wisdom that the winners o=
f the AI race will emerge from among the tech industry=E2=80=99s U.S. giant=
s. Mensch, who founded the company with two engineering-school friends, doe=
sn=E2=80=99t think enormous scale is essential =E2=80=94 or that the U.S. w=
ill necessarily dominate. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Mensch=E2=80=99s company, which has raised jus=
t over $500 million from investors including Andreessen Horowitz, remains t=
iny compared with the Goliaths of the industry. Microsoft-backed OpenAI and=
 Alphabet=E2=80=99s Google are pouring billions of dollars into training th=
e latest AI systems, leveraging their access to the specialized computer ch=
ips needed to build such systems and the fat balance sheets needed to pay f=
or the electricity those chips consume.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Mistral, named for a strong wind that blows fr=
om France, is founded in part on the idea that a lot of that money is being=
 wasted. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CWe want to be the most capital-effici=
ent company in the world of AI,=E2=80=9D Mensch said. =E2=80=9CThat=E2=80=
=99s the reason we exist.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Mensch said his new model cost less than =E2=
=82=AC20 million, the equivalent of roughly $22 million, to train. By contr=
ast OpenAI Chief Executive Sam Altman said last year after the release of G=
PT-4 that training his company=E2=80=99s biggest models cost =E2=80=9Cmuch =
more than=E2=80=9D $50 million to $100 million.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In general, we are coming out of many years of=
 venture capital exuberance in which saying =E2=80=9Cwe are competing to bu=
ild a world-changing technology, and we=E2=80=99re going to win by spending=
 slightly less money than our competitors=E2=80=9D was=C2=A0<em>not=C2=A0</=
em>a particularly appealing pitch: The <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombe=
rgbusiness.com/click/34493478.285379/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcG=
luaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjAtMDEtMzEvZG9uLXQtYmxpdHpzY2FsZS1hZ2FpbnN0LXlvdXJzZ=
